records.addlTxt: Received, Filed, and Forwarded to the Judge for review; DEBOLT REPORT
Order for Competency Examination by Department of Health Services

Defendant Beth Ann Debolt appeared by video.  Attorney Maryann Corea appeared by video for Beth Ann Debolt.  Prosecuting attorney Josh Milder in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Pretrial Conference held.  Defense raises competency pursuant to Wisc. Stat. 971.14(3).  Court suspends proceedings and ordered defendant be examined by the Forensic Unit. Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for November 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Level 5 Supervision.
Court ordered defendant to maintain ABSOLUTE SOBRIETY. 
Court ordered no possession or use of controlled substances without a valid prescription and no possession or use of dangerous weapons or firearms. 
Court reminded defendant of no contact order.
$1,000.00 Cash Bail to be returned to the person designated on the bail form.

Defendant Beth Ann Debolt in court, in custody.  Attorney Maryann Corea in court for Beth Ann Debolt.  Attorney Josh Milder in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Defense bail motion heard.  Arguments placed on the record.  Court will modify cash bail to $1,000.00 signature bond with JusticePoint supervision level 5.  Defense counsel requests additional pretrial conference date.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed. Defendant's Motion for Modification of Bail
No Contact/No Weapons Order, CKD signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Beth Ann Debolt appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Fred Richardson III appeared by video for Beth Ann Debolt. Attorney Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Skwierawski, Branch 41.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.
Status conference scheduled for September 8, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
